139: ## Setup Decisions
140: 
141: ### WalletConnect Project ID
142: 
143: **Required.** RainbowKit throws an error without it. MetaMask extension works without it (bypasses WalletConnect via browser extension), but all other wallets need it:
144: 
145: | Wallet | Works without projectId? | Why |
146: |--------|-------------------------|-----|
147: | MetaMask (browser extension) | Yes | Connects directly via browser extension, bypasses WalletConnect |
148: | MetaMask (mobile) | No | Uses WalletConnect relay — needs projectId |
149: | Coinbase Wallet | No | Uses WalletConnect relay — needs projectId |
150: | Rainbow Wallet | No | Uses WalletConnect relay — needs projectId |
151: | Any wallet without extension | No | All go through WalletConnect relay |
152: 
153: If a judge opens the app on their phone or doesn't have MetaMask installed, they can't connect without a projectId. That's a broken first impression.
154: 
155: - Free at https://cloud.reown.com (5 minutes to sign up)
156: - Store as `VITE_WALLETCONNECT_PROJECT_ID` in `.env.local`
157: - Set origin allowlist on the dashboard to your Vercel domain
158: - The projectId is inherently client-side — WalletConnect recommends allowlisting origins, not hiding the key
159: 
160: ### COOP/COEP Headers
161: 
162: **Set them.** Zama's official SDK docs (docs.zama.org) explicitly state that `useEncrypt` loads FHE WASM in a Web Worker, which requires `SharedArrayBuffer`. The required headers are:
163: 
164: ```
165: Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
166: Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
167: ```
168: 
169: **Trade-offs:** `require-corp` can break WalletConnect relay (no CORP headers), Vercel Toolbar, and some CDN assets. Use `credentialless` instead of `require-corp` for fewer breakage issues — it has broad browser support in 2026.
170: 
171: **Decision:** Set COOP/COEP in vercel.json (use `credentialless` for COEP if `require-corp` causes issues). The SDK's useEncrypt and Web Worker features need these headers. [UPDATED: June 2026 — corrected from "Do NOT set them"]
172: 
173: ### React Router 7
174: 
175: **Use Declarative Mode.** Just `react-router` with `<BrowserRouter>` + `<Routes>`. No Vite plugin, no framework config, simplest setup. For ~8 routes, this is the least friction.
176: 
177: Framework mode adds code-splitting and type safety but requires more config files (`root.tsx`, `entry.client.tsx`, `routes.ts`). Not worth it for this project size.
