526: | **ERC-7984** | Standard rules for private tokens. Same structure as ERC-20 but balances are encrypted. Only the owner can see the actual number. | Registry page: shows each confidential wrapper with its encrypted balance handle. |
527: | **Wrapping** | Converting a public token into a private token. You put 100 public USDC into a lock box, you get 100 private cUSDC back. The public tokens are locked. | Wrap page: user picks a token, enters an amount, clicks wrap. Shows approval + wrap transactions. |
528: | **Unwrapping** | Converting a private token back to a public token. You put 100 private cUSDC into the lock box, you get 100 public USDC back. The private tokens are destroyed. | Unwrap page: user picks a private token, enters an amount, clicks unwrap. Shows 2-step async flow. |
529: | **Decrypting** | Seeing your private balance. Your balance is scrambled on the blockchain. Decrypting unscrambles it so only you can see the real number. | Decrypt page: user clicks decrypt, signs a message, sees their real balance. |
530: | **EIP-712** | A standard for signing messages with your wallet. When you click "Decrypt," your wallet asks "do you want to sign this message?" — that's EIP-712. It proves you're the owner. | Explainer page (Section 4): user signs a permit, sees decryption happen. Docs page: code example of EIP-712 signing. |
531: | **FHEVM** | The encryption technology. It lets the blockchain do math on encrypted numbers without seeing the actual values. Like doing math on locked boxes without opening them. | Explainer page (Section 1): user encrypts a value, sees handle appear. Docs page: explanation of how FHE works. |
532: | **The Relayer** | A server run by Zama that decrypts your balance. It checks your signature first, then sends back the real number. Only the relayer can decrypt. | Decrypt page: shows relayer communication. Docs page: explains relayer architecture. |
533: | **The SDK** | A toolkit (npm package) that handles all the encryption/decryption/communication logic. Without it, you'd have to write hundreds of lines of code yourself. | All pages: the SDK powers every feature. Docs page: SDK reference with hook signatures. |
534: | **The Registry** | A smart contract on the blockchain that lists all official token pairs. The app reads this list to know which tokens to show. | Registry page: reads from the on-chain registry and displays all pairs. |
535: | **Allowance/Approval** | Permission you give to a contract to spend your tokens. Before wrapping, you must approve the wrapper to take your USDC. Like giving someone a key to your safe. | Wrap page: checks allowance, prompts approval if needed. |
536: | **ACL (Access Control List)** | Permissions that control who can decrypt what. The contract must grant you permission to decrypt your own balance. This happens automatically when you wrap. | Decrypt page: shows "Wrap first to enable decryption" if ACL not granted. |
